                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16751208-1-off5 t16751208-1-crimeloc2"></join>, went to serve it upon him accordingly, but fiailing in their enterprize, and being incensed by the hissing and floutings of the Shop keepers and Apprentices thereabouts, one of them drew his Hanger, and making at one of the crowd cut clean through the brims of his Hat, but by his stepping back escaped without any further harm. The tumult no way terrified hereby began to revile them more than before; insomuch that the Bayliffs (a sort of Men not very apt to take affronts) began to be so highly enraged,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="16751208003"></xptr>that of them calling to his Companions, swore in the too vulgar Prase) Damme! Draw, and we will clear the way. Whereupon 'tis said that all of them (however, as many as had swords) drew, and cutting as it were a passage thorough the crowd, till they came to the end of <placeName id="t16751208-1-crimeloc3">Turn-stile-Alley</placeName>
